	<br/>

<h2>Studios</h2>
	For this first edition, we will be staying over in renovated studios from 2012, located in the right wing of the hotel. There are three types :
	<ul>
		<li>
			Double Studio (2 persons)
			<ul>
				<li>Standard studio on one floor</li>
				<li>with 2 single beds next to each other</li>
				<li>with a kitchenette (microwave, fridge, sink and cooktops)</li>
				<li>with a table, chairs, a small sofa and a big closet</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>
			Family Studio (4 persons)
			<ul>
				<li>Duplex</li>
				<li>with a kitchenette (microwave, fridge, sink and cooktops)</li>
				<li>with a table, chairs, 2 big closets and an extra sink on floor two</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>
			Family Studio (5 or 6 persons) (see pictures below)
			<ul>
				<li>Duplex</li>
				<li>with 2 single beds and 2 bunk beds (2 people on floor one and 3 or 4 above)</li>
				<li>with a kitchenette (microwave, fridge, sink and cooktops)</li>
				<li>with a table, chairs, 2 big closets and an extra sink and toilet on floor two</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
	</ul>
	
	<br/>
	
	<img alt='rooms' src='pics/hotel/rooms.jpg' width='100%' />
	
	<br/>

	<h2>Breakfast and Dinner</h2>

	The basic package of the convention gives you access to the breakfast and dinner buffets at the restaurant of the hotel.
	<br/>
	The dinner buffet has a salad bar and a self-service area with a choice between two or three warm meals plus a dessert buffet and a self-service pump for soft drinks, light beer, red and white wine.
	
	<br/>
	<br/>
	
